.TH "keyring_restrict" 9 "keyring_restrict" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
keyring_restrict \- Look up and apply a restriction to a keyring
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" keyring_restrict
.BI "(key_ref_t keyring_ref "  ","
.BI "const char *type "  ","
.BI "const char *restriction "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "keyring_ref" 12
The keyring to be restricted
.IP "type" 12
The key type that will provide the restriction checker.
.IP "restriction" 12
The restriction options to apply to the keyring
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Look up a keyring and apply a restriction to it.  The restriction is managed
by the specific key type, but can be configured by the options specified in
the restriction string.
